  "text": "for an arbitrary constant s; note that the right-hand side is 0 because J = 0. In this class of techniques, Eqs. (1) and [CITATION_1] are solved at positions with and without sources, respectively. Reference [CITATION_2] applied the above technique with s = +1 to boundary value problems described in [CITATION_3] and achieved accelerated convergence. Such boundary value problems satisfied J = 0 everywhere, so Eq. (5) was solved throughout the entire simulation domain.",
